The paper proposes a framework for efficient neural architecture search, which is a topic that falls under the sub-field of machine learning. Specifically, the paper focuses on using task meta-features and previous model training experiments to quickly identify a good candidate architecture for a new task. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the following arXiv CS sub-categories:

- cs.LG (Machine Learning)
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence)
- cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition)
- cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing)
- cs.CL (Computation and Language)
